At Polteq I learned the basics of testing , I got my testcertifications and came into contact with the companies 'NU.nl' and 'Brick Parking'.  Eventually been working in consultation basis in these companies.

-Testjob NU.nl;
-Testjob Brickparking;

Erman was the only tester in the organization of NU.nl and was the responsible employee for Testing. Erman studied the user stories, created test cases, and executed these test cases. These tests were executed on NU.nl website, the app 'NU' and the intern CMS of NU.nl. Erman reported the test results in Excel and also communicated these results to the programmers.
NU.nl worked within the Agile method. Every two weeks was the start of a new sprint. Erman had during sprints frequent contact with members of the team. Meetings consisted of scaling and prioritizing user stories.

-Investigating user stories;
-Writing test cases;
-Scaling and prioritizing Testcases;
-Choosing testing techniques;
-Executing test cases;
-Report testresults;
-Communicate testresults with the developers / product owners;

The assignment at Yellow Brick was to perform regression testing on the Billing System. Erman has, in addition to carrying out the tests, the test team supported by establishing test cases, to place the test cases in the tracking system, arranged test cases for review and, if necessary, edited/corrected the test cases.

-To meet with the basic principles of the test;
-Perform regression testing;
-Writing test cases;
-Review test cases and correct if necessary;
-Place the tests in the tracking system;
-Support the other testers at their work

The Thesis was investigated and executed at GGD Zaanstreek-Waterland. My investigation was to advice how the departments ‘Facilities’ and ‘ICT’ could improve and optimalise the support of the tool ‘Facilitor’ to their deparment. 
Also tasks regarding (mobile) phones were executed during this period. This was an initiative from the intern.

-	Draw up Plan of Approach;
-	Investigate the current processes of the both deparments;
-	Interview employees who work in the deparments, the backoffice of Facilitor and other employees in GGD Zaanstreek-Waterland;
-	Execute bottlenecks to analyse the interviews;
-	Investigate and conclude how  the tool ‘Facilitor’  could improve and optimalise their support to the deparments ‘Facilites’ and ‘ICT’;
-	Investigate how the advices could be implemented;
-	Provide cellphones to the employees;
-	Help employees in case of problems/emergencies;
-	Keep in touch with the operator  ‘Intercity’ in the event of network disruptions;
-      Perform test work on functionality of the 'Facilitor' tool and the GGD Zaanstreek-Waterland website; 
-	Report testfindings to ICT department;

Executing the business assignment. The task  was to map the security of CTM Solution's internal ICT infrastructure and to provide advice for improving safety.
Furthermore, the customer service of CTM Solution's electronic tender tool was supported. Customers reached us  by telephone and by mail.
